(Necromancy)
Level: Clr 9
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 20-foot radius
Saving Throw: Fortitude negates

Mass Harm releases destructive negative energy upon all living enemies in the area of effect. The caster makes ranged touch attacks against each of those creatures; each one that get hit must Save vs. Fortitude or lose all but one hit point. The DC is the same as that of the 6th-level Harm spell. Allied undead in the area of effect are instead healed to full health as per a Heal spell.~
@1126    = ~Iron Body~
@1127    = ~Iron Body 
(Transmutation)
Level: Sor/Wiz 8, Helm 8
Range: Caster
Duration: 1 round / level
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell transforms the caster's body into living iron, granting him several powerful resistances and abilities. While the spell is in effect, the caster has 15/- resistance to fire, cold, and all forms of physical damage, but also +15 vulnerability to electricity. Spells that affect respiration or the physiology of the caster are ignored completely, such as poison, blindness, deafness, and disease to name a few, and the caster becomes too heavy to knock back with spells like Gust of Wind, Throw or Repulsion. In addition, the caster gains a +8 bonus to strength and constitution and a -8 dexterity penalty. Unfortunately, the caster's movement becomes slow and awkward under the weight of his new body, setting his movement rate to half its normal rate, and he receives a -2 penalty to casting speed.~
@1857    = ~Death Fog~
@1858    = ~Death Fog
(Transmutation)
Level: Sor/Wiz 6
Range: Sight of Caster 
Duration: 10 rounds
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: None

This spell brings forth a billowing cloud of acidic fog. The thick fog limits movement to 50% of a creature's current movement rate. In addition, all creatures caught within the fog take 3d6 points of acid damage per round.~
@37955     = ~Malavon's Corrosive Fog~
